body.value: Amy: Okay, here we go. You will be actually done with the Saturn cycle part of it, starting in November. That part will disappear for a little bit unless it goes retrograde. Let me just check. 20, 21. Yes, it does go retrograde, it does hit 15. What will happen is, okay, November, there'll be a release of energy, but then you'll be working very intensely on this external changing stuff. Then, coming back in May, you're going to be experiencing a reconnection. Oh, actually that's May. Yes, May of '82, you're going to be experiencing a reconnection to the work issue, and that will continue all of May and all of June, because it just sits on 15, which is your Saturn. It just sits there for the whole month. The whole month of June of 1982, you'll be going through a lot of changes around your work, and around opening up your work, and your power. Then, it sits for the first couple of weeks in July of '82 as well, and then it passes on, and you're done. The end of July of '82, you're done with that part of your Saturn cycle, but you are still having Saturn through your 12th house. You're still dealing with things externally, and things are still coming up to make you deal with letting go of your limitations, letting go of your negative energy, and that continues until it hits seven degrees of Scorpio, which is not until October of 1983. You still have another year after that of dealing with the external stuff. Then, in October of '83, you start having Saturn through your first house, and what this does, Cherrie, is this then forces you to really accept your power. You then, instead of the externals making the changes, you make the changes, and you create your own power. The first house is the house of self-identity. You then start accepting power inside of yourself. It's the power to be yourself. You're not going in the closet and looking around for who you're going to be. It's like you just strip off. You're just-- This whole period of time is a stripping off of negative energy. Anything that keeps you from totally being yourself, totally accepting your true power. Then, that continues until six degrees of Sagittarius, which is, let me just check this. It's retrograde. Yes, let's see. [silence] Until October of 1986, so you can see that this is, as I said-
Cherrie: Oh, wow. [laughs]

Amy: -it's a six-year cycle. It's a six-year cycle. The thing you have to realize is that, this next six-year period usually is unbelievable. I mean, who you will be in 1986, will be completely different from who you are now, not in a negative way, and not in someone you don't know, but you are going to be empowering yourself, and you'll be accepting your power. This is this incredible transformational time for you. It is a time of initiation, and you can see yourself. That's why you have visions of who you're going to be, and it does scare the shit out of you. The thing you have to realize is that, you have these six years to prepare for it. You have these six years to slowly become that divine warrior that you need to be. Yes, you have accepted a very intense destiny in this lifetime. That means that you have to accept your power. You have to accept being a warrior. You have to accept being known. You have to accept being public, which is very scary.
Cherrie: Yes, definitely.

Amy: Very scary. You know your Libra freaks out. Your Libra looks at that and says, "I can't do that. No, I'm not here." Yet, you know you have no choice. You set it up, you have to accept it, and yet, it will be slow enough. See, that is the purpose of this six-year cycle, Cherrie, is that it will be slow enough, so that it doesn't overwhelm you, so that you know that it's not going to be too much, so that you know that this is the thing that you really need to do. Also, that you know that, it's just what you have to do inside of yourself. The thing that you're really working on, is really allowing yourself to have a sense of truth. It's really allowing yourself to trust this destiny for these next six years. The trouble is that, you feel like you're on a journey, and you don't have a roadmap. The reason for that, Cherrie, is so that you do not fuck it up.
Cherrie: Right.

Amy: [chuckles] So that you can't get in your own way, and the thing you have to realize is, "Okay, you don't have a roadmap, but you do have signs all the way." It'll be the kind of thing, where it's like getting the little piece of paper and saying, "Go down the street and turn right." You think, "Oh God, what's down the street and turn right?" As soon as you do that, you get another piece of paper that says, "Now cross, Morrissey Boulevard." You do that and then you get another piece of paper, and it says, "Okay, now count five blocks and go to the left," and you do that. It's the thing where, okay, you might not know what's going to happen in six months. You might not know what's going to happen in two weeks, but that doesn't matter, because your overall process is being guided, and because this is a process of you becoming yourself, and accepting your destiny. Yes, it's very scary and very intense, but you have a whole lot of support. The universe supports you in it. It's what you have to do. You will have guidance every single step of the way, and protection every single step of the way. That's a very, very important energy for you. Extremely important.
Cherrie: I feel like I've been through a journey. [laughs]

Amy: I know. Really. As you can see, now for the next year or so, you're really working with this external stuff. All I can say, the key I can give to you is, whatever comes up, if something knocks on your door and says, "Deal, deal," know that it's something that you really have to do. Don't try to ignore it. Realize that it's something that you really need to work with, and it has a key to your truth inside of it. Now, [chuckles] the next thing to tell you about, is the fact that you do have this really packed 12th house, and it really does say that this is a lifetime for you to release karma, because the 12th house is the house of releasing karma. It's the 12th house is the house of self-forgiveness, and self-acceptance. That's why I'm really stressing the self-forgiveness, because it's saying that you can't do what you really have to do, unless you're open to this truth. Unless you are open to forgiving yourself for any past negative energies, and really accepting the truth inside of yourself, accepting the love inside of yourself, accepting the knowledge that you are exactly who you have to be, and you must totally accept that energy, and let that love come forth inside of you. Now, another thing that's going on, is that you do have this Pluto conjunct the south node in the 10th house.

Amy: What that says is that you have a very important life's work to do in this lifetime, as you well know. That it's not just a work, it's not a job, it's not even a career. It is a whole lifestyle. It's saying what you have to do with your life, it has to be complete. The people you're with and what you do, and the things that you experience, and what you dream about, and lovers and friends, everything, all has to connect to that work. It's saying that, it's not just for yourself. It's not just so that you can repay karma, or so that you can achieve your destiny, or so that you can evolve. It's not even just for the planet. It's for the whole universe. That's the thing you have to accept, is that you have this divine work to do. You have to be a channel for it. That it's really a scary thing, but it's an absolutely right thing. It's also saying that you can only be as good for it as you are inside of yourself. You might have met people who have great reps, and then you meet them and it's like, "Ugh, this person's a real drag." What it is, it's because maybe they can detach themselves. Their personal life can be very different from their political, or their work life, but for you, it's the same. It's saying that whoever you are inside, you are outside, and that's why you feel so much pressure, because everything you do, your work, your friends, your lovers, your living situation, the things you think about, the things you dream about, the things you eat, everything connects to who you are and to your destiny, and to your work. That's because of that Pluto energy. However, you also have this south node in Leo. Now, you may have already done this, but anyone who has a south node in their 10th house has some work that they that they have got to do, so that is karmic. It's like they've got to repair some karma because, for some reason, they weren't allowed to do this work in a past life, something stopped them. It's like they're stuck there. They can't go on to their true work until they deal with the leavings of a past life.

Amy: Now, as an example, one woman I knew who had this, was a person, who ever since she was little, had this overwhelming knowledge that she had to go to law school. What happened was that in a past life, she had been a woman, and women at the time were not allowed to be lawyers. Her brother had been this lawyer, and yet she had been the one who had done all the work, because her brother was a lush, and he really couldn't get anything together. She had been the one who researched it all and prepared the briefs, and did all the work, and yet she had gotten no credit for it at all. In this lifetime, she had to complete law school. It was just this thing. She went to law school, she did the whole thing. She took the bar, she practiced for like a little over two years, and then she completely dropped it. Everybody thought she was crazy, but what it was, is she had to complete the energy. She had to complete the cycle.

Cherrie: I think that might be what has just recently happened with me in teaching. Where I always just thought, that's what I had to do, and when I did it, I went through everything I had to do it. Now. I don't want it.

Amy: That's great. That's fine, because [chuckles] then it means that you've completed the karma, and you can go onto your true work. It's saying this was a stumbling block in the way of your true work, because you couldn't do it for some reason. Maybe you just were prevented from being a real teacher in a past life. You really wanted to do it, but you couldn't do it. Now that you've done it, now that you can go on and do the stuff that you really have to do. It's really-- It could be so, because in that past life, you really had a very powerful position. It could be, you kept yourself in past lives from being a teacher, because you really felt that, somehow, you would misuse the power again. It's almost like you had to prove to yourself that you could communicate to people, and communicate very forcefully, and very well, and not blow it.
Cherrie: Right.

Amy: Have that kind of adoration people get for teachers, be the guide and facilitator for people's souls, and yet know you did it right. Now, that you've known that you've done it right, you can let it go.
Cherrie: That's how it feels. Yes.

Amy: The neat thing about that too, Cherrie, is that Jupiter rules teaching, and Jupiter is the real key to both the T-Square and the [unintelligible] It's interesting that you chose teaching, because it was right there saying, "Well, this is something you had to do," because this way you really got to break through the energy, which is really, really neat for you. Great. Now, that you felt you really did it, now you can be open in your Saturn cycle to your true work, and to let that work really guide you, to let that work really open you, to let that work really make it okay for you to accept the truth, and to know that this is exactly what it is that you have to do.
Cherrie: What I do is I write. When I'm told that, I always-- There's just such dread, and also anticipation. You know what I mean? I mean both of those things, because it's hard work.

Amy: Oh, of course. The thing too is that, see, mercury is conjuncture sun, and mercury is mental energy. It's also writing a communication. Conjuncture sun, it says you have such a need to communicate. As I said, it's not just for yourself, it's for the universe, and because it's in the 11th house, the 11th house is the breakthrough of illusion. It says that what you feel you have to communicate is the truth, you just feel this overwhelming need. Yet, what happens, is that victim part of you gets in there and freaks out, and says, "Are you crazy? They're going to get you for that. You can't communicate the truth. You cannot possibly do it. You can't, you can't do it. You can't, you can't, you can't." It makes you just really, really, really fearful, and really totally freaked out by that energy. It just really makes you overwhelmed by the energy inside of yourself, especially, because I get the image that I feel in that past life, that you were the victim. It wasn't like you were just a victim. I feel like you really meant, you really wanted to communicate the truth. You really saw some things that were really true. I feel like, you started off life being a pretty oppressed woman, and just having a really hard time having a family that was really not supportive to you, and a situation that was not supportive to you. I feel like you got married very young, and had children, and it was very intense, because you really didn't know what you were doing. Then, I feel like your husband in that lifetime died, and that was this incredible breaking transformation point for you, because you were forced to be really strong, and that allowed you to see how strong that you really were. I get the image that, what happened, I don't know, I just get this image that was really recent, and that you were Native American, you were Indian.
Cherrie: That's interesting.

Amy: You really tried to-- It was like you were fighting against a lot of stuff. You weren't just fighting against the prejudice of White people, and politically trying to fight for rights. I feel like you are also fighting the men who are also Indian, and fighting their energy. See, I get the hit that you got married off really young, and then when your husband died, it was in some kind of brawl, or some kind of fight. Then, it was this thing where you weren't expected to be alone. It's was almost like you were expected to, at least, take on a male lover, and have him protect you, and do the stuff. It's like you decided, it was almost sudden, you got this flash, and it was like, "My whole life I've never been able to be strong, and I can be strong." It was almost like-- I mean, it was like you never even really liked your husband all that much. It was like you just got married, because you were coerced into it, and you did it, and you had these kids, and it was your whole life. You were just pushed into one thing after another. When you saw it, and he terrified you. He was this incredibly intense person, who was very strong, and really very abusive in his own way. It was like the fact that he was-- His life, which just snuffed out. It was like somebody knifed him, and you just was like, "If somebody could just do that to this person who was really intense and strong and super macho, well, then maybe that's not the way, maybe that's not strength." It was this moment of reckoning, and you just decided, "I'm going to do it. I'm going to do it." It's like you got really strong, but the thing was, that you still carried this incredible victimization energy with you, and you started speaking out. You didn't just speak out to like the men around you, and speak out politically in your own circle, but you started speaking out to people who were a lot more powerful, even than they, and people who maybe had political power. You started saying, "No, we're not going to accept this, and I'm not going to accept this." The thing was though, is that you really got into this thing of almost preparing for your own doom, in a way. It was like you just really thought, "Well, I know I'm going to get it for doing this, but I have to do it to break through the karma." At the same time, it was almost like you couldn't really accept the fact that you didn't have to be a victim.
Cherrie: Right.

Amy: It was so ingrained in you. Even though you came to this realization, maybe in your mid-30s, you didn't have to be a victim anymore. In that particular way, it was still so in you, you couldn't let it go. That finally, it got to this point where you knew, it was like you had some threats made on you, and you knew that if you went to confront this person, something really bad was going to happen. At the same time, it was like you almost accepted it as your fate, even to the point where you went through this real strange thing of saying "goodbye" in a really special way to your kids. It's like you knew, it was like you really knew you were going to die, but at the same time, it's like you wouldn't consciously accept it. You just went through this thing, and you went to confront this person, and this really incredibly disgusting person. It was like, "Oh, we're going to teach this little woman a lesson." It was almost like all they meant to do was rough you up, and the next thing you knew, they were murdering you. It was like this really incredible thing. You were just attacked by all these men. It was this incredibly horrible, horrible experience for you, but at the same time, in a way, it was less horrible than it might have been, because you immediately left your body. It was like, even when they were raping you, it was like you left your body, because it was like, you just knew that it was your death. It was like you said, "Okay, don't even fight because that you set this up." At the same time, you were so angry at yourself, it was like you just really split with your consciousness, and also at the same time, it was terrible. The thing is, that in that lifetime, you did really mean, it was like you did speak up, and you did start this whole process that you're into now. The thing you have to realize, though, is that every once in a while, that part of you is so fearful of what you're going to say, because of what happened. The thing you have to realize is that, that fear you experience, yes, it's a real fear, and yes, it does happen, but it's not going to happen to you in this lifetime. The reason why you fear it so much, is because it did already happen to you. That feeling, that victim part of you that says, "Oh, you'll get it." If you stand up and you expect the truth, and you really communicate the truth, and you really are who you are, well, you're going to get it. There's no way you're going to escape it, because it's going to happen to you. You have to realize that, that is not a premonition, Cherrie. That is a memory.
Cherrie: Right. That's an important distinction.

Amy: That you have to do it anyway. An important way for you to allow yourself to communicate what you have to communicate, is to realize that you do have to release that victim part of you. You have to let her go, because she's the one that gets so scared. Yet, it's like, it's okay to say to her, "Look, you don't have to do this anymore. You can become pure energy, and give me the light. I'll carry it as a torch. I promise you, I'll do what you wanted to do in that lifetime you couldn't do." It's like really making a commitment to yourself, to your destiny, and when you make that commitment, totally, not just partially, but totally, then the fear will disappear. That's just such an incredible energy for you. I think that's what I have to say for now. [chuckles] In a way, it might have been good that we didn't have all that much time, because I feel like your chart is just so heavy, it's just so intense, that it's almost like, it's too much to go through all at once. Also, because it's just-- There's so much. I feel like I could talk about your chart for hours and hours and hours. Like I said, I feel like I've just scratched the surface. I feel like I said the things that I felt would be most important to say at this time.

Cherrie: Oh, they seem essential. I mean, I couldn't have-- If I could have asked you ahead of time, what I'd want you to say, it's like you mentioned the things that just to me are real critical, it's like I know what you're saying. It's real timely for me to hear it.
Amy: Oh, good. That's great. Okay, so I do want you to know that the option, you can always come back for more.
[End of Recording]
